At the meeting, the International Whaling Commission (IWC) will vote on several resolutions including whether Japan could expand its whaling quota.
Critics call Japan's program commercial whaling in disguise.
Japan, Norway and other nations this year are expected to take more than 1,550 whales.
Japan has no cultural tradition of hunting whales in the Southern Ocean.
Australia and other anti-whaling countries condemn research whaling as a guise for commercial whaling.
Japan is against new whale sanctuaries and proposed that this issue be pushed off the agenda at the opening of the commission's annual general assembly in South Korea.
